properties.headline: HURRICANE WARNING — Catastrophic Category 4 landfall near Fort Myers
properties.description: Hurricane Ian is making landfall near Fort Myers with maximum sustained winds of 150 mph. This is an EXTREMELY DANGEROUS situation. Catastrophic storm surge of 12–18 ft above ground level expected along the immediate coast. EVACUATE NOW if you have not already done so.

properties.headline: Hurricane Warning in effect for SW and Central Florida
properties.description: HURRICANE WARNING IN EFFECT. Hurricane Ian is forecast to produce catastrophic winds, storm surge, and inland flooding across SW and Central Florida counties.

properties.areaDesc: Charlotte Harbor and Pine Island Sound
properties.headline: Life-threatening Storm Surge Warning — 10–15 ft inundation
properties.description: STORM SURGE WARNING. Life-threatening inundation of 10–15 ft above ground level is expected along Charlotte Harbor, Pine Island Sound, and the mouth of the Caloosahatchee River.

properties.headline: Storm Surge Warning — 5–10 ft above ground level for Gulf coast
properties.description: STORM SURGE WARNING. Life-threatening inundation of 5–10 ft above ground level expected along the Gulf coast of Collier through Pinellas counties.

properties.areaDesc: Broward; Miami-Dade; Palm Beach; Martin; St. Lucie; Indian River; Okeechobee; Highlands
properties.headline: Tornado Watch 550 in effect until 8 PM EDT for South Florida
properties.description: TORNADO WATCH. Conditions are highly favorable for tornado development across South and Central Florida as outer bands of Hurricane Ian rotate onshore.

properties.headline: TORNADO WARNING — Confirmed tornado near Boca Raton
properties.description: At 3:29 PM EDT, a confirmed tornado was located near Boca Raton, moving north at 30 mph. TAKE COVER NOW.

properties.areaDesc: Orange; Osceola; Seminole; Polk; Lake; Volusia; Brevard
properties.headline: Flash Flood Warning for Central Florida — 6–10 inches already fallen
properties.description: At 2:45 PM EDT, Hurricane Ian continues to produce torrential rainfall across Central Florida. 6–10 inches of rain have fallen with another 3–5 inches expected. TURN AROUND, DON'T DROWN.

properties.headline: Tropical Storm Warning — Sustained tropical storm conditions imminent
properties.description: TROPICAL STORM WARNING. Tropical storm conditions are expected within 12 hours across Gulf Coast counties north of the Hurricane Warning area.

properties.headline: Coastal Flood Warning — 3–5 ft inundation along Atlantic coast
properties.description: COASTAL FLOOD WARNING. Dangerous coastal flooding is expected along the Atlantic coast of Florida due to offshore flow and large breaking waves from Hurricane Ian.

properties.headline: High Wind Warning — Sustained winds 40–50 mph, gusts to 65 mph
properties.description: HIGH WIND WARNING. Sustained winds of 40 to 50 mph with gusts up to 65 mph expected across NE Florida as the remnants of Ian move rapidly inland.

properties.headline: Flood Watch through Thursday for SE Georgia — Ian remnants bring 4–8 inches
properties.description: FLOOD WATCH. The remnants of Hurricane Ian are expected to produce 4–8 inches of rainfall with isolated amounts up to 12 inches across SE Georgia, leading to dangerous flooding.

properties.description: FLOOD WATCH. Ian's remnants will produce 3–5 inches of rainfall with locally higher amounts possible across the Low Country of South Carolina.
